title: Taylor Swift - F. Scott Fitzgerald
body:
Deep dive much. Stretching it much.

Back in 2014 Miss Swift graced the cover of People magazine, a DOUBLE ANNIVERSARY (double album, 13th year of swift - the kind of anniversary she would celebrate) edition. For this cover she recreated the first ever People magazine cover, starring one Mia Farrow, starring as Daisy in GATSBY by F. Scott Fitzgerald. Going back to their roots, back to where it all started. 

“I once was poison ivy, but now I’m your daisy“ Don’t Blame ME.

For more lyric coincidences with Gatsby read “https://slate.com/culture/2017/11/taylor-swift-s-great-gatsby-fixation.html”

@taylorswift @taylornation
